title: Week 5: Top Box Scores
text: Week 5: Top Box Scores Ben Mitchum Talk about it in the kansasgridiron Message Boards Week Five in the Sunflower State saw the higher classifications posting big numbers across the board, but a pair of small school players shone the brightest, setting new state records for total touchdowns and TD receptions.KansasGridiron goes around the Wheat State to recap some of the top performances in this week's Top Box Scores. Passing Once again, 4A-I Bishop Miege quarterback Carter Putz had a big night, throwing for 338 yards. Putz had a pair of TD passes and ran for two more in a 56-20 victory over 5A Blue Valley West. Grant Hilliard of 2A Sedgwick was 17 of 21 for 267 yards and two TDs in a 44-14 victory over 2A Salina-Sacred Heart. He also ran for 132 yards and two more TDs on the night.6A Wichita Northwest quarterback Kevin Folsom passed for 275 yards and four TDs through the air, with four more scores on the ground. Northwest defeated 6A Wichita West, 69-28.5A Blue Valley North signal caller Joey Dolan completed 32 of 50 pass attempts for 274 yards and three TDs in a 28-27 upset win over Class 6A power Blue Valley. Rushing In 8-Man I action, Garrett Myers of Waverly rushed for 420 yards on 30 carries and a new Kansas 8-Man record 12 total touchdowns in a 83-44 win over Pleasanton. 11 rushing TDs and a pick-6 for Myers on the memorable night.Dalton Peters of Class 5A Salina Central rushed for 307 yards and 4 TDs in a 51-13 victory over 6A Haysville. Peters is third in the state in rushing behind Osawatomie's Riley England, and Ulysses' Ian Rudzik .Class 4A-II saw the aforementioned Riley England have another big night, as the Osawatomie RB gains 287 yards and 6 TDs in a 49-24 win over Anderson County. England leads the state with 1,331 rushing yards and 16 scores.Quarterback Reshean Holloway of Class 3A Russell rushed for 284 yards and four scores in a 42-16 defeat of Southwestern Heights. He also impacted the game through the air, adding another 115 yards and a TD. Receiving Class 4A-II Holcomb saw Christian Merz haul in five receptions for 158 yards and two TDs in a 44-12 victory over Colby. Tristan Allen of Class 3A Nemaha Central had six catches for 151 yards in a win over 4A-II perennial power Holton, 27-13. Martese Mullins of 6A Wichita Northwest hauled in 11 passes for 135 yards and two TDs in the win over Wichita West. 3A Doniphan West receiver Cooper Leach had 10 catches for 187 yards and a new single-game record six TDs in a 55-20 defeat of Class 2A Maranatha-Immaculata. For the season, Leach already has 15 TD receptions and leads the state with 665 receiving yards. Top Defensive Performances The Olathe East defense had six interceptions in a 25-14 victory over Sunflower League foe Shawnee Mission Northwest. Cornerback Dion Union had three picks, while safety Kameron Barnes pulled down a pair of INTs in Class 6A action.Ellinwood linebacker Jordan Duvall logged 23 tackles, three tackles for loss, and two sacks in a 46-20 defeat to Solomon in 8-Man I.In 8-Man II, South Barber LB Spencer Kimmel registered 20 tackles in a 32-22 victory over South Haven.
